reviews.snippet:
I have recently visited this place, here is my honest review about this place -
For more visit my Instagram Page- @mandar.ayachit

1. Ambiance - this place has a good ambiance, 2 floor cafe where 1st floor has sitting arrangements for family and friends. Which has really good vibe. Ground floor has cafe, stores, shopping centre.

2. Service- this place was crowded, there will be some waiting period to get place, but personally I didn’t like the service, it was way slow and kind of rude. We have asked for a glass of water but the service boy was some rude and directly told it will take time to get water. Which was not at all good behaviour.

3. Food - Tea was really a good in taste and enough quantity. As compared to price this was ok. One time visit for me. Bun Maska was really good. Bun was really fresh and tasty.

4. Parking - enough parking space is available.

reviews.snippet:
If you’re looking for a late-night tea fix, Niloufer Chai is the place to be. Even at 12:30 midnight, the place is buzzing with a huge crowd, which says a lot about its popularity. Be prepared to wait—both at the cash counter and the tea counter—but the wait is worth it.

The chai itself is incredibly fresh and refreshing, living up to the hype. The strong, bold flavors make it perfect for those who enjoy a robust tea experience.

The ambiance might be a bit chaotic due to the crowd, but if you’re into the energetic, street-side tea culture, you’ll love it. Definitely a go-to spot for a late-night tea craving!

reviews.snippet:
I regularly visit Cafe Niloufer, and it has become one of my favorite spots for a good cup of tea. The tea here is truly amazing—strong, flavorful, and served piping hot, just the way it should be. What makes the experience even better is pairing the tea with their Osmania biscuits. The combination is a classic and offers the perfect balance of flavors, making every visit satisfying and comforting.

The atmosphere at Cafe Niloufer is always lively, yet there's a sense of warmth and familiarity that keeps me coming back. Whether you're catching up with friends or just taking a break, it's a great place to relax and enjoy a quick snack. I would definitely recommend others to visit this place, especially tea lovers looking for that perfect blend and a nostalgic taste of Hyderabad.

reviews.snippet:
Cafe Niloufer lived up to its reputation as one of Hyderabad's iconic spots. I discovered it through YouTube, where it received glowing reviews, so I had to visit during my trip. Despite the crowd, the service was impressively quick, showcasing their efficiency.

I tried the Osmania Biscuit, Niloufer Tea Single, and Maska Bun. The Maska Bun stole the show—perfectly buttery and indulgent. Even though I’m not a tea lover, I genuinely enjoyed their tea, which complemented the biscuits wonderfully.

The lively atmosphere added to the charm, making it a memorable experience to enjoy such simple yet delicious food amidst a bustling crowd. Cafe Niloufer is a must-visit for anyone exploring Hyderabad!

reviews.snippet: Caffé Niloufer is a well-loved spot in Hyderabad, known for its Niloufer Special Chai and a variety of delicious sweets, cakes, and snacks. The hygiene and quality of their products are top-notch, and they follow strict standards in preparation. While the Himayatnagar branch stands out with its better parking and more accessible layout, the Lakdikapul branch struggles with parking and crowd management, especially on weekends. Despite the parking issues at one location, the overall experience is pleasant, with a relaxed atmosphere and great tasting food. It’s a reliable choice for tea lovers, families, and anyone craving a sweet treat.

details.vegetarian_options: Caffé Niloufer offers a good variety of veg options, including cakes, sweets, and snacks. Their Niloufer Special Chai is a must-try, and the sweets are a hit. The selection is diverse enough for vegetarians, but there could be a few more options for those with more specific dietary preferences, especially in savory snacks. Overall, it’s a solid choice for vegetarians.
details.dietary_restrictions: Caffé Niloufer takes care to maintain hygiene and quality, using measured content for their ingredients. While they offer a variety of items, including sweets and cakes, those with lactose intolerance or specific dietary needs may find limited options, as many items contain milk or butter. However, their commitment to hygiene and proper ingredient management makes it a safe place for most customers.
details.parking: The parking at the Lakdikapul branch is a major drawback. There is no dedicated parking for customers, and people often have to park on the street, which can lead to illegal or prohibited parking. On the other hand, the Himayatnagar branch offers separate and better parking, making it a much more convenient option for those driving.
details.kid_friendliness: Caffé Niloufer is relatively kid-friendly, with a spacious environment, especially at the Himayatnagar branch. The menu includes a variety of non-alcoholic drinks and sweets that kids can enjoy. However, on busy days, the crowd can make it a bit difficult for families with young children to relax comfortably. Still, it’s a decent spot for a family outing, especially during less crowded hours.
details.wheelchair_accessibility: Caffé Niloufer has somewhat limited wheelchair accessibility. While the Himayatnagar branch is more accessible with easier entry, the Lakdikapul branch has some challenges, especially in terms of uneven paths and lack of ramps. It's manageable but not ideal for individuals with mobility issues.

reviews.snippet:
Cafe Niloufer in Hyderabad is a must-visit for tea lovers. Their tea is rich and flavorful, often compared to Karachi Bakery’s, and truly lives up to the hype. Apart from tea, they offer delicious snacks like veg puffs, Osmania biscuits, fresh bread, and their famous Malai Bun, which pairs perfectly with chai.

The cafe also serves a variety of other food items like biryanis and chole bhature. While I didn’t get a chance to try them, they looked incredibly tempting. The place is always buzzing with people, which adds to the lively vibe, though seating is limited and it can get crowded during peak hours. Despite this, the service is quick, so you won’t have to wait too long.

If you’re looking for an authentic Hyderabadi tea experience with some tasty snacks and tempting food options, Cafe Niloufer is definitely worth a visit.

reviews.snippet:
Classic Hyderabadi Vibes at Café Niloufer – Red Hills

If you’re in Hyderabad and looking for an authentic Irani café experience, Café Niloufer in Red Hills is the place to be. I visited during my vacation and was treated to the city’s legendary combo – maska bun and chai – and I must say, it absolutely lived up to the hype.

The chai is rich, strong, and perfectly brewed, while the maska bun is soft, buttery, and melts in your mouth. It’s simple yet incredibly satisfying, especially when enjoyed hot and fresh.

That said, be prepared for a crowded atmosphere. This place is always buzzing with locals and tourists alike, which speaks to its popularity. Seating can be tight, and you might need to wait a bit, but once that first sip of chai hits, it’s all worth it.

A must-visit for chai lovers and anyone wanting to soak in true Hyderabadi flavors and energy
